17
00:00:40,069 --> 00:00:41,190
by giving in to the demands

18
00:00:41,190 --> 00:00:43,579
of the atheist Chinese Communist Party.

19
00:00:43,579 --> 00:00:46,850
According to a senior Vatican source speaking
to Reuters,

20
00:00:46,850 --> 00:00:49,359
“A framework accord between the Vatican
and China

21
00:00:49,359 --> 00:00:51,819
on the appointment of bishops is ready

22
00:00:51,819 --> 00:00:53,850
and could be signed in a few months.”

23
00:00:53,850 --> 00:00:55,649
We’ve covered how the Pope recently

24
00:00:55,649 --> 00:00:58,350
asked two Chinese bishops to either retire

25
00:00:58,350 --> 00:01:00,999
or step aside for two other bishops

26
00:01:00,999 --> 00:01:04,239
approved of by the Chinese Communist Party.

27
00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:05,239
And yes,

28
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:07,650
one of them had been excommunicated.

29
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:11,880
But I guess he’s being...re-communicated.

30
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,080
And now, there’s a total of 7

31
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:15,280
Chinese state-approved bishops

32
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:17,210
the Pope is considering approving.

33
00:01:17,210 --> 00:01:19,920
Two of them apparently have families.

34
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:22,690
Look, I know what you’re thinking:

35
00:01:22,690 --> 00:01:25,390
Catholic bishops aren’t supposed to be married.

36
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:26,760
Well, don’t worry.

37
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:27,760
They’re not.

38
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:30,380
They just have just mistresses.

39
00:01:30,380 --> 00:01:32,410
And deep in the Pacific Ocean,

40
00:01:32,410 --> 00:01:35,710
the Chinese regime is placing acoustic sensors.

41
00:01:35,710 --> 00:01:38,060
They “could be used to study oceans”...

42
00:01:38,060 --> 00:01:40,750
and definitely not anything else.

43
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:42,240
Those acoustic listening devices

44
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:45,050
are in no way related to the nearby

45
00:01:45,050 --> 00:01:47,280
US military base in Guam.

46
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,930
Neither are they some kind of attempt

47
00:01:48,930 --> 00:01:50,610
to track foreign ships.

48
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:53,490
So don’t even go there.

49
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:55,950
And in a totally unrelated matter,

50
00:01:55,950 --> 00:01:57,780
the Philippines has changed its mind

51
00:01:57,780 --> 00:02:00,840
about joint undersea exploration with China.

52
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,370
I mean yes,

53
00:02:02,370 --> 00:02:04,920
the Philippines and China have competing claims

54
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:07,320
to territory in the South China Sea,

55
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:10,409
but this is a perfectly friendly decision.

56
00:02:10,409 --> 00:02:12,319
But, you know,

57
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:14,519
the Philippines will also “chase off foreign
ships

58
00:02:14,519 --> 00:02:16,900
conducting research in its territorial waters.”

59
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:19,370
Yeah, foreign ships.

60
00:02:19,370 --> 00:02:20,650
From any country.

61
00:02:20,650 --> 00:02:23,849
That includes China.

62
00:02:23,849 --> 00:02:26,330
And in another a totally unrelated matter,

63
00:02:26,330 --> 00:02:28,620
China might be testing the world’s first

64
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:30,980
ship-mounted rail gun.

65
00:02:30,980 --> 00:02:33,560
A rail gun is an electromagnetic weapon

66
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,599
with the power to sink a warship

67
00:02:35,599 --> 00:02:38,569
and the precision to shoot down a satellite.

68
00:02:38,569 --> 00:02:40,920
For scientific purposes of course.

69
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:44,040
The US is also testing rail guns.

70
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:47,599
Those can fire a round at about 5,000 miles
per hour

71
00:02:47,599 --> 00:02:50,779
hitting a target almost 100 miles away.

72
00:02:50,779 --> 00:02:55,750
The catch—each round costs about million
dollars.

73
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:59,120
But rail guns aren’t the only weapons that
are a threat.

74
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,730
North Korea is now just a few months away

75
00:03:01,730 --> 00:03:05,280
from being able to hit the US with a nuke.

76
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,900
And it seems nuclear proliferation

77
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:08,700
is making a comeback everywhere!

78
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:11,680
I read it in the New York Times Style section.

79
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:15,859
According to U.S. disarmament ambassador Robert
Wood,

80
00:03:15,859 --> 00:03:19,989
China and Russia are also pushing nuclear
development.

81
00:03:19,989 --> 00:03:20,989
You get a nuke!

82
00:03:20,989 --> 00:03:21,989
You get a nuke!

83
00:03:21,989 --> 00:03:24,489
Everybody gets a nuke!

84
00:03:24,489 --> 00:03:27,030
This comes shortly after a statement by the
Pentagon

85
00:03:27,030 --> 00:03:30,249
that China and Russia are becoming a greater
threat

86
00:03:30,249 --> 00:03:32,959
than Islamic terrorism.

87
00:03:32,959 --> 00:03:33,959
But the Pentagon is known

88
00:03:33,959 --> 00:03:36,459
for making the occasional snafu.

89
00:03:36,459 --> 00:03:38,849
In a report about the China nuclear threat,

90
00:03:38,849 --> 00:03:40,769
